    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>WELSH UTILITY BATTLE OVER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Suzanne Kapner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Kapner, Suzanne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nomura International withdraws from takeover battle for Hyder PLC, troubled Welsh utility company (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The big Japanese investment bank Nomura International withdrew from the takeover battle for Hyder P.L.C., a troubled Welsh utility, paving the way for Western Power Distribution of the United States to buy Hyder. Nomura said it would not appeal a decision by a British regulatory panel to allow Western Power's winning bid of 365 pence, or $5.48, a share, which Nomura had contended was made after the regulator's deadline. The deal values Hyder at $:565 million, or about $848 million.</p>
        <p>Suzanne Kapner (NYT)</p>
      </block>
